rdf:RDF.dcterms:title: ABCD EFG
rdf:RDF.dc:description: ABCD EFG (ABCD Extended for Geosciences) is an extension for the [[ABCD 2|ABCD XML Schema]] (Access to Biological Collection Databases) for use with palaeontological, mineralogical and geological digitalized collection data.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AllocthonousMaterial
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for descriptive elements related to transported material ranging from glacial erratics to meteorites

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Alteration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for describing metasomatic, metamorphic or diagenetic changes to units

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AlterationDegree
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text describing the degree of alteration or metamorphic phase that has affected a rock. [This element may need to be split into hydrothermal mineralogical change and metamorphic phases]

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AlterationType
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text describing the type of change that has taken place e.g. chloritisation, migmatisation, cataclastic brecciation etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When the analysis was carried out.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-DateText
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text to allow for vague dates or description of analysis period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-DayNumberBegin
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Julian day number in the year for the exact date or for the beginning day of a period

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-DayNumberEnd
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Julian day number of the last day in a period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-ExactDate
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Uses DateTime element from ABCD.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-ExactDate-DateText
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The date in text format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-ISODateTimeBegin
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The exact date (and time) or beginning of a period, expressed in a modified ISO/ANSI 8601 standard structured format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-ISODateTimeEnd
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The end of a period expressed in a modified ISO/ANSI 8601 standard structured format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-PeriodExplicit
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Set to True if the event takes place for the period indicated, set to False if it occurs at some point of time during the period, not filled if unknown or no period specified.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-TimeOfDayBegin
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Time of day in hours from midnight for an exact point in time or for the beginning of a time period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-TimeOfDayEnd
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Time of day in hours from midnight for the end of a time period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisDateTime-TimeZone
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The time zone to which the time-of-day data refer.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisReferences
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for 1 or more references related to the analysis.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisReferences-AnalysisReference
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Individual documentary reference linked to an analysis. Uses abcd:Reference Type

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisReferences-CitationDetail
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Specific page, figure or illustration number(s) within the reference.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisReferences-TitleCitation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Formal citation for a paper or electronic publication.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AnalysisReferences-URI
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Universal Resource Identifier - Path to electronic source of document.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Articulation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text description of the articulation in the preserved specimen - applies to invertebrate shells and exoskeletons as well as vertebrate skeletons. e.g. articulated, dis-articulated, single valves etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: AssemblageOrigin
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text description relating to the mode of origin of the assemblage e.g. unknown, allochthonous, autochthonous, paraautochthonous etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: BaselineDatum
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Text - what is the baseline e.g. top of borehole or base of measured section

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Bioerosion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text description of damage due to biological action, such as, boring worms and sponges.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Borehole
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for details specific to boreholes and wells. Does not contain spatial reference as this and details of platform etc. are under Gathering in main ABCD schema - but they could be copied to make an independent schema.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: BottomSurface
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for details of bottom surface of layer or stratum.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: BottomSurfaceFeature
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Text describing features at the base of a layer or stratum.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Certainty
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Degree of certainty associated with the date determination e.g. unknown, certain, uncertain, possibly, known wrong.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CommissionedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Company or organisation who commissioned the borehole or well.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Completeness
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text descrbing the degree of completeness of the specimen e.g. complete, cephalon only, but may describe completeness of a part e.g. complete skull.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Contractor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The drilling contractor who carried out the work.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalForm
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container element for describing the crystal form of a mineral unit.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalFormText
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text description of crystal form.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Individual measurement or fact related to a crystal unit - container for standard MeasurementOrFact complex type from main schema.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-Accuracy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Statement of accuracy of measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-AppliesTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Depending on the use of the type, this can further specify the actual part measured. For example, a measurement of temperature may be a surface, air or sub-surface measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-CitationDetail
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Specific page, figure or illustration number(s) within the reference.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-Duration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Duration of measurement in time.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-IsQuantitative
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Flag indicating if the value represents the numerical result of a quantitative measurement (TRUE) or a descriptor with textual or categorical result (FALSE).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-LowerValue
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Lower or only value or fact text.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-MeasuredBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Attribution of the measurement to a Person

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-MeasurementDateTime
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date and/or Time the measurement was taken.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-MeasurementOrFactReference
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference (publication) where this measurement was taken from.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-MeasurementOrFactText
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text alternative to atomised version.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-Method
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Method used to make measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-Parameter
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Describes type of measurement or fact, such as width, abundance, circumference, temperature etc. or color etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-TitleCitation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Formal citation for a paper or electronic publication.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-URI
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Universal Resource Identifier - Path to electronic source of document.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-UnitOfMeasurement
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Unit of measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurement-UpperValue
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Upper value where there is a range.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: CrystalMeasurements
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for measurements of crystal physical and chemical characteristics.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DatingQualifier
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Allows for qualification of date terms e.g. early/lower, middle, late/upper.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DiageneticChange
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text for describing any physical and chemical changes that took place in a sediment during the lithification process e.g. compaction, cementation, recrystallisation, dolomitisation and replacement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DipDegrees
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The dip in degrees of laminae or stratal surfaces in this layer.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DistanceFromBaseline
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Number representing distance measured.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: DrillMethod
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: How the borehole or well was drilled e.g. reverse circulation drilling, diamond coring, percussion drilling, auger drilling, rotary/barber drilling etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: EarthScienceSpecimen
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for details that generally relate to the management of earth science specimens and their individual stratigraphic age (which may be different or more specific than that recorderd for the gathering site or the host rock.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Encrustation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text description of biological encrustations, such as oysters and tube worms.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: FeedingPredationTraces
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text description relating to aspects of feeding and predation e.g. ammonite with bite mark from plesiosaur, shell drilled by predatory gastropod etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The geologist(s) and or organisation responsible for logging the borehole and or maintaining the borehole record.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-Abbreviation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Restricted to 50 characters maximum length, including blanks (recommended to be shorter!). Label abbreviations are especially important when displaying information in a tabular format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-FullName
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Preferred form of personal name for display as a string.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-GivenNames
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The name given to a person as a personal name (= first or christian name in western cultures, including 'middle initials') may contain several words ('Ana Maria', 'Jerry B.'). Applicable only to persons. (vCard:N.Given + vCard:N.Middle)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-InheritedName
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Family names, generational names, clan name, parents/grandparents personal names, etc. This (= last name in western cultures) may be compound ('Fischer von Waldheim', 'da Selva', 'Silvano Morales'). Depending on culture it is not necessarily the name of the parents nor common to the married couple and children, thus 'family name' should be avoided even though used in vCard. (vCard:N.Family)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-Name
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Full organization or corporate name in multiple languages (en: 'Botanical Garden of ...', de: 'Botanischer Garten von ...'). vCard:Org.OrgName). The Label mechanism also supports acronyms / abbreviations (no vCard equivalent!).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-OrgUnit
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (vCard:OrgUnit)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-OrgUnits
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: If the contact contains no person definition: the unit within the organization the agent represents; else a list of the various organisational units to which a person may belong. (vCard:OrgUnit)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-Organisation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Organisation type from the abcd schema.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-Person
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Person type from the abcd schema.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-PreferredName
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: May differ from the first given name: second given name, nickname ('Bob' for 'Robert'), etc. (vCard:Nickname)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-Prefix
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Prefix to inherited name that should be output before name, but is usually not included in sorting. Examples: 'von', 'Lord'. Compare Title for 'Prof', 'Dr.' (vCard:N.Prefix)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-Representation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Language-specific label representation. [ATTR: language]

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-SortingName
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The full name with the elements in preferred sorting sequence (vCard: Sort-String).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-Suffix
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Suffix to name that should be output after name, regardless whether it is in sorting sequence (Inherited, Given) or not. Examples: 'Jun.', 'III.'. (vCard:N.Suffix)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Geologists-Text
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Label text in a specific language.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Hazard
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for describing hazards that may be associated with the specimen e.g. radioactive, toxic, carcinogens etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HazardText
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Free text describing any hazards that may be associated with the specimen/unit e.g. is it radioactive, poisonous, carcinogenic?

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HoleDiameter
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Diameter of the borehole in milliimetres.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HoleDirection
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Direction and inclination of the borehole or well.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HostRockStratigraphy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Container for any stratigraphic determination specific to the host rock. For instance the gathering site may include a range of stratigraphic horizons whilst the unit host rock may represent just one. The unit itself might be different if it is allochthonous in origin. Minerals may be of a different age from their host rock.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HostRockStratigraphy-Bed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The smallest division of a named stratified series normally with well defined division from adjacent deposits.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HostRockStratigraphy-BiostratigraphicAttribution
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A single declaration of a fossil zone or subzone.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HostRockStratigraphy-BiostratigraphicAttribution-Abbreviation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Restricted to 50 characters maximum length, including blanks (recommended to be shorter!). Label abbreviations are especially important when displaying information in a tabular format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HostRockStratigraphy-BiostratigraphicAttribution-Accuracy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Statement of accuracy of measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: HostRockStratigraphy-BiostratigraphicAttribution-AppliesTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Depending on the use of the type, this can further specify the actual part measured. For example, a measurement of temperature may be a surface, air or sub-surface measurement.
